mod-dav-acl (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * added acl-xpath tool into tools directory. acl-xpath can extract individual
    element & attribute & text node contents from result files
  * principal REPORTs only allowed with collections
  * lintian build cleanups
  * added manpage for acl-test-cli, acl-principals and acl-xpath
  * separated some common utilities into a library

 -- Jari Urpalainen <jari@urpalainen.fi>  Fri, 17 Aug 2012 15:15:00 +0300

mod-dav-acl (0.1.8) unstable; urgency=low

  * owner stored also within eas (speedup of regular puts)
  * removed the usage of some ugly macros

 -- Jari Urpalainen <jari.urpalainen@nokia.com>  Thu, 27 Jan 2011 10:44:00 +0200

mod-dav-acl (0.1.7) unstable; urgency=low

  * propfind tests used wrong filename context
  * read-acl and read-current-user-privilege-set can be aggregated into read
    privilege with AclAggregatedCurrentUserPrivilegeSet and AclAggregatedAcl
    options
  * acl_prop_check only runs read-acl or read-current-user-privilege-set tests
    depending on the above settings. propfind is based first on having read
    privilege on the resource, and those above tests may additionally be needed.
  * fixed 2 sizeof bugs

 -- Jari Urpalainen <jari.urpalainen@nokia.com>  Wed, 12 Jan 2011 16:20:00 +0200

